======================================================================
PART 7: The Alon Bound — Maximum H ≤ c·n^{3/2}·n!/2^n
======================================================================

Alon bound analysis: max H ≤ c·n^{3/2}·n!/2^n
log(max H / (n!/2^{n-1})) / log(n):
  n= 3: max/mean = 2.000000, log ratio / log n = 0.6309
  n= 4: max/mean = 1.666667, log ratio / log n = 0.3685
  n= 5: max/mean = 2.000000, log ratio / log n = 0.4307
  n= 6: max/mean = 2.000000, log ratio / log n = 0.3869
  n= 7: max/mean = 2.400000, log ratio / log n = 0.4499
  n= 8: max/mean = 2.098413, log ratio / log n = 0.3564
  n= 9: max/mean = 2.368254, log ratio / log n = 0.3924
  n=10: max/mean = 2.221517, log ratio / log n = 0.3466
  n=11: max/mean = 2.439506, log ratio / log n = 0.3719

  CONCLUSION: max H / mean H appears BOUNDED
  The Paley tournament gives max/mean ≈ 2.4 for large p ≡ 3 mod 4
  This suggests max H ~ c · n!/2^{n-1} with c ≈ e (Euler's number?)

  e = 2.718282
  Max odd-n ratio (n=11): 2.439506

